==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amitosis
<hw>Am`i*to"sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. See
<er>A-</er> not, and <er>Mitosis</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld>
<def>Cell division in which there is first a simple cleavage of the
nucleus without change in its structure (such as the formation of
chromosomes), followed by the division of the cytoplasm; direct cell
division; -- opposed to <contr>mitosis</contr>. It is not the usual mode
of division, and is believed by many to occur chiefly in highly
specialized cells which are incapable of long-continued multiplication,
in transitory structures, and in those in early stages of
degeneration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amitotic</ent>⟦br⟧
